citations:
    citation-adwd-the-queensguard:
        source: source-adwd
        properties:
            locator: "The Queensguard"
            text_from_source: "I am the queen's man still. Today, tomorrow, always, until my last breath, or hers. Barristan Selmy refused to believe that Daenerys Targaryen was dead."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Barristan Selmy POV. Set after Daenerys's disappearance on Drogon. Hizdahr zo Loraq rules as king, replacing Barristan's Queensguard with pit fighters (Goghor the Giant, Khrazz, the Spotted Cat, Belaquo Bonebreaker). Skahaz mo Kandaq has been stripped of command of the Brazen Beasts and replaced by Hizdahr's cousin Marghaz zo Loraq. Strong Belwas is gravely ill from poisoned locusts. Barristan reflects on his long service: knighted by Aegon the Unlikely, given the white cloak by Jaehaerys II after slaying Maelys the Monstrous during the War of the Ninepenny Kings. He reflects on his rescue of Aerys II from Duskendale. Skahaz meets Barristan secretly in the pyramid stables wearing a cat mask. He reveals Hizdahr's confectioner was coerced by the Sons of the Harpy to poison the locusts (the man's nine-year-old daughter was killed in nine pieces as payment). Skahaz reports Volantis has launched its fleet against Meereen, and that Hizdahr intends to open the gates to the Volantenes. Barristan agrees to speak to Grey Worm about joining a planned assault on the Yunkai'i forces. He insists Hizdahr must not be harmed until guilt is proven. He trains a group of young squires — fewer than 30 remaining from more than 60 who started — to be knights for Daenerys."
